    "title": "ISS recommends votes against Facebook CEO Zuckerberg, 4 other directors",
    "locations": [],
    "highlightText": "",
    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "BOSTON, May 16 (Reuters) - Proxy adviser Institutional Shareholder Services on Wednesday recommended investors withhold their support from five Facebook Inc directors, including Chief Executive Mark Zuckerberg and Chief Operating Officer Sheryl Sandberg, citing issues including the social media company’s lack of a formal nominating committee.\nISS also suggested investors vote “for” shareholder proposals calling for the company to study establishing a board committee on risk management, and to report on content management controversies, according to copy of its recommendations seen by Reuters. (Reporting by Ross Kerber in Boston Editing by Matthew Lewis)\n ",
